33namespace webrtc {
34
35// Forward declarations.
36class FrameEncryptorInterface;
37class RateLimiter;
38class RemoteBitrateEstimator;
39class RtcEventLog;
40class RTPSender;
41class Transport;
42class VideoBitrateAllocationObserver;
43
44class RtpRtcpInterface : public RtcpFeedbackSenderInterface {
45 public:
46 struct Configuration {
47 Configuration() = default;
48 Configuration(Configuration&& rhs) = default;
49
50 // True for a audio version of the RTP/RTCP module object false will create
51 // a video version.
52 bool audio = false;
53 bool receiver_only = false;
54
55 // The clock to use to read time. If nullptr then system clock will be used.
56 Clock* clock = nullptr;
57
58 ReceiveStatisticsProvider* receive_statistics = nullptr;
59
60 // Transport object that will be called when packets are ready to be sent
61 // out on the network.
62 Transport* outgoing_transport = nullptr;
63
64 // Called when the receiver requests an intra frame.
65 RtcpIntraFrameObserver* intra_frame_callback = nullptr;
66
67 // Called when the receiver sends a loss notification.
68 RtcpLossNotificationObserver* rtcp_loss_notification_observer = nullptr;
69
70 // Called when we receive a changed estimate from the receiver of out
71 // stream.
72 RtcpBandwidthObserver* bandwidth_callback = nullptr;
73
74 NetworkStateEstimateObserver* network_state_estimate_observer = nullptr;
75 TransportFeedbackObserver* transport_feedback_callback = nullptr;
76 VideoBitrateAllocationObserver* bitrate_allocation_observer = nullptr;
77 RtcpRttStats* rtt_stats = nullptr;
78 RtcpPacketTypeCounterObserver* rtcp_packet_type_counter_observer = nullptr;
79 // Called on receipt of RTCP report block from remote side.
80 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/10679): Consider whether we want to use
81 // only getters or only callbacks. If we decide on getters, the
82 // ReportBlockDataObserver should also be removed in favor of
83 // GetLatestReportBlockData().
84 RtcpCnameCallback* rtcp_cname_callback = nullptr;
85 ReportBlockDataObserver* report_block_data_observer = nullptr;
86
87 // Estimates the bandwidth available for a set of streams from the same
88 // client.
89 RemoteBitrateEstimator* remote_bitrate_estimator = nullptr;
90
91 // Spread any bursts of packets into smaller bursts to minimize packet loss.
92 RtpPacketSender* paced_sender = nullptr;
93
94 // Generates FEC packets.
95 // TODO(sprang): Wire up to RtpSenderEgress.
96 VideoFecGenerator* fec_generator = nullptr;
97
98 BitrateStatisticsObserver* send_bitrate_observer = nullptr;
99 SendSideDelayObserver* send_side_delay_observer = nullptr;
100 RtcEventLog* event_log = nullptr;
101 SendPacketObserver* send_packet_observer = nullptr;
102 RateLimiter* retransmission_rate_limiter = nullptr;
103 StreamDataCountersCallback* rtp_stats_callback = nullptr;
104
105 int rtcp_report_interval_ms = 0;
106
107 // Update network2 instead of pacer_exit field of video timing extension.
108 bool populate_network2_timestamp = false;
109
110 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameTransformerInterface> frame_transformer;
111
112 // E2EE Custom Video Frame Encryption
113 FrameEncryptorInterface* frame_encryptor = nullptr;
114 // Require all outgoing frames to be encrypted with a FrameEncryptor.
115 bool require_frame_encryption = false;
116
117 // Corresponds to extmap-allow-mixed in SDP negotiation.
118 bool extmap_allow_mixed = false;
119
120 // If true, the RTP sender will always annotate outgoing packets with
121 // MID and RID header extensions, if provided and negotiated.
122 // If false, the RTP sender will stop sending MID and RID header extensions,
123 // when it knows that the receiver is ready to demux based on SSRC. This is
124 // done by RTCP RR acking.
125 bool always_send_mid_and_rid = false;
126
127 // If set, field trials are read from |field_trials|, otherwise
128 // defaults to webrtc::FieldTrialBasedConfig.
129 const WebRtcKeyValueConfig* field_trials = nullptr;
130
131 // SSRCs for media and retransmission, respectively.
132 // FlexFec SSRC is fetched from |flexfec_sender|.
133 uint32_t local_media_ssrc = 0;
134 absl::optional<uint32_t> rtx_send_ssrc;
135
136 bool need_rtp_packet_infos = false;
137
138 // If true, the RTP packet history will select RTX packets based on
139 // heuristics such as send time, retransmission count etc, in order to
140 // make padding potentially more useful.
141 // If false, the last packet will always be picked. This may reduce CPU
142 // overhead.
143 bool enable_rtx_padding_prioritization = true;
144
145 // Estimate RTT as non-sender as described in
146 // https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3611#section-4.4 and #section-4.5
147 bool non_sender_rtt_measurement = false;
148
149 private:
150 RTC_DISALLOW_COPY_AND_ASSIGN(Configuration);
151 };
152
153 // Stats for RTCP sender reports (SR) for a specific SSRC.
154 // Refer to https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3550#section-6.4.1.
155 struct SenderReportStats {
156 // Arrival NPT timestamp for the last received RTCP SR.
157 NtpTime last_arrival_timestamp;
158 // Received (a.k.a., remote) NTP timestamp for the last received RTCP SR.
159 NtpTime last_remote_timestamp;
160 // Total number of RTP data packets transmitted by the sender since starting
161 // transmission up until the time this SR packet was generated. The count
162 // should be reset if the sender changes its SSRC identifier.
163 uint32_t packets_sent;
164 // Total number of payload octets (i.e., not including header or padding)
165 // transmitted in RTP data packets by the sender since starting transmission
166 // up until the time this SR packet was generated. The count should be reset
167 // if the sender changes its SSRC identifier.
168 uint64_t bytes_sent;
169 // Total number of RTCP SR blocks received.
170 // https://www.w3.org/TR/webrtc-stats/#dom-rtcremoteoutboundrtpstreamstats-reportssent.
171 uint64_t reports_count;
172 };
173
174 // **************************************************************************
175 // Receiver functions
176 // **************************************************************************
177
178 virtual void IncomingRtcpPacket(const uint8_t* incoming_packet,
179 size_t incoming_packet_length) = 0;
180
181 virtual void SetRemoteSSRC(uint32_t ssrc) = 0;
182
183 // **************************************************************************
184 // Sender
185 // **************************************************************************
186
187 // Sets the maximum size of an RTP packet, including RTP headers.
188 virtual void SetMaxRtpPacketSize(size_t size) = 0;
189
190 // Returns max RTP packet size. Takes into account RTP headers and
191 // FEC/ULP/RED overhead (when FEC is enabled).
192 virtual size_t MaxRtpPacketSize() const = 0;
193
194 virtual void RegisterSendPayloadFrequency(int payload_type,
195 int payload_frequency) = 0;
196
197 // Unregisters a send payload.
198 // |payload_type| - payload type of codec
199 // Returns -1 on failure else 0.
200 virtual int32_t DeRegisterSendPayload(int8_t payload_type) = 0;
201
202 virtual void SetExtmapAllowMixed(bool extmap_allow_mixed) = 0;
203
204 // Register extension by uri, triggers CHECK on falure.
205 virtual void RegisterRtpHeaderExtension(absl::string_view uri, int id) = 0;
206
207 virtual int32_t DeregisterSendRtpHeaderExtension(RTPExtensionType type) = 0;
208 virtual void DeregisterSendRtpHeaderExtension(absl::string_view uri) = 0;
209
210 // Returns true if RTP module is send media, and any of the extensions
211 // required for bandwidth estimation is registered.
212 virtual bool SupportsPadding() const = 0;
213 // Same as SupportsPadding(), but additionally requires that
214 // SetRtxSendStatus() has been called with the kRtxRedundantPayloads option
215 // enabled.
216 virtual bool SupportsRtxPayloadPadding() const = 0;
217
218 // Returns start timestamp.
219 virtual uint32_t StartTimestamp() const = 0;
220
221 // Sets start timestamp. Start timestamp is set to a random value if this
222 // function is never called.
223 virtual void SetStartTimestamp(uint32_t timestamp) = 0;
224
225 // Returns SequenceNumber.
226 virtual uint16_t SequenceNumber() const = 0;
227
228 // Sets SequenceNumber, default is a random number.
229 virtual void SetSequenceNumber(uint16_t seq) = 0;
230
231 virtual void SetRtpState(const RtpState& rtp_state) = 0;
232 virtual void SetRtxState(const RtpState& rtp_state) = 0;
233 virtual RtpState GetRtpState() const = 0;
234 virtual RtpState GetRtxState() const = 0;
235
236 // Returns SSRC.
237 virtual uint32_t SSRC() const = 0;
238
239 // Sets the value for sending in the RID (and Repaired) RTP header extension.
240 // RIDs are used to identify an RTP stream if SSRCs are not negotiated.
241 // If the RID and Repaired RID extensions are not registered, the RID will
242 // not be sent.
243 virtual void SetRid(const std::string& rid) = 0;
244
245 // Sets the value for sending in the MID RTP header extension.
246 // The MID RTP header extension should be registered for this to do anything.
247 // Once set, this value can not be changed or removed.
248 virtual void SetMid(const std::string& mid) = 0;
249
250 // Sets CSRC.
251 // |csrcs| - vector of CSRCs
252 virtual void SetCsrcs(const std::vector<uint32_t>& csrcs) = 0;
253
254 // Turns on/off sending RTX (RFC 4588). The modes can be set as a combination
255 // of values of the enumerator RtxMode.
256 virtual void SetRtxSendStatus(int modes) = 0;
257
258 // Returns status of sending RTX (RFC 4588). The returned value can be
259 // a combination of values of the enumerator RtxMode.
260 virtual int RtxSendStatus() const = 0;
261
262 // Returns the SSRC used for RTX if set, otherwise a nullopt.
263 virtual absl::optional<uint32_t> RtxSsrc() const = 0;
264
265 // Sets the payload type to use when sending RTX packets. Note that this
266 // doesn't enable RTX, only the payload type is set.
267 virtual void SetRtxSendPayloadType(int payload_type,
268 int associated_payload_type) = 0;
269
270 // Returns the FlexFEC SSRC, if there is one.
271 virtual absl::optional<uint32_t> FlexfecSsrc() const = 0;
272
273 // Sets sending status. Sends kRtcpByeCode when going from true to false.
274 // Returns -1 on failure else 0.
275 virtual int32_t SetSendingStatus(bool sending) = 0;
276
277 // Returns current sending status.
278 virtual bool Sending() const = 0;
279
280 // Starts/Stops media packets. On by default.
281 virtual void SetSendingMediaStatus(bool sending) = 0;
282
283 // Returns current media sending status.
284 virtual bool SendingMedia() const = 0;
285
286 // Returns whether audio is configured (i.e. Configuration::audio = true).
287 virtual bool IsAudioConfigured() const = 0;
288
289 // Indicate that the packets sent by this module should be counted towards the
290 // bitrate estimate since the stream participates in the bitrate allocation.
291 virtual void SetAsPartOfAllocation(bool part_of_allocation) = 0;
292
293 // Returns bitrate sent (post-pacing) per packet type.
294 virtual RtpSendRates GetSendRates() const = 0;
295
296 virtual RTPSender* RtpSender() = 0;
297 virtual const RTPSender* RtpSender() const = 0;
298
299 // Record that a frame is about to be sent. Returns true on success, and false
300 // if the module isn't ready to send.
301 virtual bool OnSendingRtpFrame(uint32_t timestamp,
302 int64_t capture_time_ms,
303 int payload_type,
304 bool force_sender_report) = 0;
305
306 // Try to send the provided packet. Returns true iff packet matches any of
307 // the SSRCs for this module (media/rtx/fec etc) and was forwarded to the
308 // transport.
309 virtual bool TrySendPacket(RtpPacketToSend* packet,
310 const PacedPacketInfo& pacing_info) = 0;
311
312 // Update the FEC protection parameters to use for delta- and key-frames.
313 // Only used when deferred FEC is active.
314 virtual void SetFecProtectionParams(
315 const FecProtectionParams& delta_params,
316 const FecProtectionParams& key_params) = 0;
317
318 // If deferred FEC generation is enabled, this method should be called after
319 // calling TrySendPacket(). Any generated FEC packets will be removed and
320 // returned from the FEC generator.
321 virtual std::vector<std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend>> FetchFecPackets() = 0;
322
323 virtual void OnPacketsAcknowledged(
324 rtc::ArrayView<const uint16_t> sequence_numbers) = 0;
325
326 virtual std::vector<std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend>> GeneratePadding(
327 size_t target_size_bytes) = 0;
328
329 virtual std::vector<RtpSequenceNumberMap::Info> GetSentRtpPacketInfos(
330 rtc::ArrayView<const uint16_t> sequence_numbers) const = 0;
331
332 // Returns an expected per packet overhead representing the main RTP header,
333 // any CSRCs, and the registered header extensions that are expected on all
334 // packets (i.e. disregarding things like abs capture time which is only
335 // populated on a subset of packets, but counting MID/RID type extensions
336 // when we expect to send them).
337 virtual size_t ExpectedPerPacketOverhead() const = 0;
338
339 // **************************************************************************
340 // RTCP
341 // **************************************************************************
342
343 // Returns RTCP status.
344 virtual RtcpMode RTCP() const = 0;
345
346 // Sets RTCP status i.e on(compound or non-compound)/off.
347 // |method| - RTCP method to use.
348 virtual void SetRTCPStatus(RtcpMode method) = 0;
349
350 // Sets RTCP CName (i.e unique identifier).
351 // Returns -1 on failure else 0.
352 virtual int32_t SetCNAME(const char* cname) = 0;
353
354 // Returns remote NTP.
355 // Returns -1 on failure else 0.
356 virtual int32_t RemoteNTP(uint32_t* received_ntp_secs,
357 uint32_t* received_ntp_frac,
358 uint32_t* rtcp_arrival_time_secs,
359 uint32_t* rtcp_arrival_time_frac,
360 uint32_t* rtcp_timestamp) const = 0;
361
362 // Returns current RTT (round-trip time) estimate.
363 // Returns -1 on failure else 0.
364 virtual int32_t RTT(uint32_t remote_ssrc,
365 int64_t* rtt,
366 int64_t* avg_rtt,
367 int64_t* min_rtt,
368 int64_t* max_rtt) const = 0;
369
370 // Returns the estimated RTT, with fallback to a default value.
371 virtual int64_t ExpectedRetransmissionTimeMs() const = 0;
372
373 // Forces a send of a RTCP packet. Periodic SR and RR are triggered via the
374 // process function.
375 // Returns -1 on failure else 0.
376 virtual int32_t SendRTCP(RTCPPacketType rtcp_packet_type) = 0;
377
378 // Returns send statistics for the RTP and RTX stream.
379 virtual void GetSendStreamDataCounters(
380 StreamDataCounters* rtp_counters,
381 StreamDataCounters* rtx_counters) const = 0;
382
383 // A snapshot of Report Blocks with additional data of interest to statistics.
384 // Within this list, the sender-source SSRC pair is unique and per-pair the
385 // ReportBlockData represents the latest Report Block that was received for
386 // that pair.
387 virtual std::vector<ReportBlockData> GetLatestReportBlockData() const = 0;
388 // Returns stats based on the received RTCP SRs.
389 virtual absl::optional<SenderReportStats> GetSenderReportStats() const = 0;
390
391 // (REMB) Receiver Estimated Max Bitrate.
392 // Schedules sending REMB on next and following sender/receiver reports.
393 void SetRemb(int64_t bitrate_bps, std::vector<uint32_t> ssrcs) override = 0;
394 // Stops sending REMB on next and following sender/receiver reports.
395 void UnsetRemb() override = 0;
396
397 // (NACK)
398
399 // Sends a Negative acknowledgement packet.
400 // Returns -1 on failure else 0.
401 // TODO(philipel): Deprecate this and start using SendNack instead, mostly
402 // because we want a function that actually send NACK for the specified
403 // packets.
404 virtual int32_t SendNACK(const uint16_t* nack_list, uint16_t size) = 0;
405
406 // Sends NACK for the packets specified.
407 // Note: This assumes the caller keeps track of timing and doesn't rely on
408 // the RTP module to do this.
409 virtual void SendNack(const std::vector<uint16_t>& sequence_numbers) = 0;
410
411 // Store the sent packets, needed to answer to a Negative acknowledgment
412 // requests.
413 virtual void SetStorePacketsStatus(bool enable, uint16_t numberToStore) = 0;
414
415 virtual void SetVideoBitrateAllocation(
416 const VideoBitrateAllocation& bitrate) = 0;
417
418 // **************************************************************************
419 // Video
420 // **************************************************************************
421
422 // Requests new key frame.
423 // using PLI, https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc4585#section-6.3.1.1
424 void SendPictureLossIndication() { SendRTCP(kRtcpPli); }
425 // using FIR, https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5104#section-4.3.1.2
426 void SendFullIntraRequest() { SendRTCP(kRtcpFir); }
427
428 // Sends a LossNotification RTCP message.
429 // Returns -1 on failure else 0.
430 virtual int32_t SendLossNotification(uint16_t last_decoded_seq_num,
431 uint16_t last_received_seq_num,
432 bool decodability_flag,
433 bool buffering_allowed) = 0;
434};
435
436} // namespace webrtc
